label: Doxycycline
description: A prescription antibiotic medication used to treat a variety of bacterial infections, including respiratory, urinary tract, and skin infections, by inhibiting the growth and spread of bacteria in the body.

label: Vyvanse
description: A prescription medication used to treat attention deficit hyperactivity disorder (ADHD) and binge eating disorder (BED) by affecting certain neurotransmitters in the brain to improve focus and reduce impulsivity and hyperactivity.

label: Truvada
description: A prescription medication used as pre-exposure prophylaxis (PrEP) to help reduce the risk of HIV infection in individuals at high risk, as well as for the treatment of HIV when used in combination with other antiretroviral drugs.

label: Hydroxyzine
description: A prescription antihistamine medication used to relieve itching, anxiety, and allergic reactions by blocking the effects of histamine in the body and having a calming effect on the central nervous system.

label: Aricept
description: A prescription medication used to treat Alzheimer''s disease by increasing levels of certain neurotransmitters in the brain to improve cognitive function and slow the progression of symptoms.

label: Aspirin
description: An over-the-counter medication that is used to relieve pain, reduce inflammation, and lower fever, while also having antiplatelet properties that can help reduce the risk of blood clot formation in some medical conditions.

label: Xanax
description: A prescription medication used to treat anxiety and panic disorders by producing a calming effect in the brain.

label: Singulair
description: A prescription medication used to treat asthma and allergy symptoms by blocking substances in the body that cause inflammation and constriction of the airways.

label: Lamictal
description: A prescription medication primarily used to treat epilepsy and bipolar disorder by stabilizing mood and reducing the frequency of seizures.

label: Mucinex
description: An over-the-counter medication that contains guaifenesin and is used to relieve chest congestion and thin mucus in the airways, making it easier to cough up and clear.

label: Carboplatin
description: A chemotherapy drug used to treat various types of cancer by interfering with the growth and spread of cancer cells in the body.

label: Atorvastatin
description: A prescription medication used to lower cholesterol levels in the blood and reduce the risk of cardiovascular events like heart attacks and strokes.

label: Benadryl
description: An over-the-counter antihistamine medication used to relieve symptoms of allergies, such as itching, sneezing, runny nose, and hives, by blocking the effects of histamine in the body.

label: Docusate
description: An over-the-counter stool softener used to relieve constipation by making it easier for water to penetrate and soften dry or hard stools.

label: Symbicort
description: A prescription medication used to treat asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) by combining two active ingredients (budesonide and formoterol) to reduce airway inflammation and improve breathing.

label: Ivermectin
description: A medication primarily used to treat parasitic infections in humans and animals by disrupting the nervous systems of certain parasites and causing their paralysis and death.

label: Zoloft
description: A prescription medication that belongs to the class of antidepressants known as selective serotonin reuptake inhibitors (SSRIs), used to treat depression, anxiety disorders, and other mental health conditions by increasing serotonin levels in the brain.

label: Humalog
description: A brand of insulin, used for the treatment of diabetes, to help control blood sugar levels by lowering high blood sugar when taken before or after meals.

label: Metformin
description: A prescription medication commonly used to treat type 2 diabetes by helping to lower blood sugar levels and improve the body''s response to insulin.

label: Loperamide
description: An over-the-counter medication used to relieve diarrhea by slowing down intestinal contractions and reducing bowel movements.

label: Triamcinolone
description: A prescription corticosteroid medication used to treat various inflammatory conditions, such as allergies, skin disorders, and arthritis, by reducing inflammation and suppressing the immune response in the body.

label: Cialis
description: A prescription medication used to treat erectile dysfunction (ED) and symptoms of benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) by increasing blood flow to the penis and relaxing the muscles in the prostate and bladder.

label: Entereg
description: A prescription medication used to accelerate the recovery of gastrointestinal function after abdominal surgery by reducing the risk of postoperative ileus, a condition where normal bowel movements are delayed.

label: Omeprazole
description: A medication available over-the-counter and by prescription that reduces stomach acid production and is used to treat conditions such as heartburn, gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD), and stomach ulcers.

label: Allopurinol
description: A prescription medication used to lower high levels of uric acid in the body and prevent or manage conditions like gout and kidney stones that are associated with excess uric acid.

label: Minoxidil
description: An over-the-counter medication used topically to promote hair growth and treat male and female pattern baldness by widening hair follicles and extending the hair growth cycle.

label: Zyrtec
description: An over-the-counter antihistamine medication used to relieve allergy symptoms such as sneezing, runny nose, itching, and watery eyes by blocking the effects of histamine in the body.

label: Acyclovir
description: A prescription medication used to treat viral infections like herpes by inhibiting the growth and spread of the herpes simplex virus.

label: Lisinopril
description: A prescription medication used to treat high blood pressure (hypertension) and heart failure by relaxing blood vessels and improving blood flow, reducing the workload on the heart.

label: Levothyroxine
description: A prescription medication used to treat hypothyroidism (an underactive thyroid) by providing the body with synthetic thyroid hormone to regulate metabolism and other essential functions.

label: Budesonide
description: A corticosteroid medication available in various forms, such as inhalers and nasal sprays, used to treat inflammatory conditions like asthma, allergies, and inflammatory bowel disease by reducing inflammation and suppressing the immune response in the affected areas.

label: Oxybutynin
description: A medication used to treat overactive bladder and urinary incontinence by relaxing bladder muscles and reducing the frequent urge to urinate.

label: Ambien
description: A prescription medication used to treat insomnia by affecting certain chemicals in the brain to promote sleep and reduce difficulties in falling asleep or staying asleep.

label: Methyltestosterone
description: A synthetic androgen hormone used as a prescription medication to treat conditions associated with testosterone deficiency in males, such as delayed puberty or hormonal imbalances.

label: Sumatriptan
description: A prescription medication used to treat migraines and cluster headaches by narrowing blood vessels in the brain and reducing pain and other symptoms associated with these types of headaches.

label: Meloxicam
description: A prescription nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) used to relieve pain and reduce inflammation in conditions like arthritis by inhibiting the production of certain chemicals in the body that cause pain and swelling.

label: Alendronate
description: A prescription medication used to treat osteoporosis and prevent fractures by slowing down bone loss and increasing bone density in postmenopausal women and some men.

label: Oxycodone
description: A prescription opioid medication used to manage moderate to severe pain by changing how the brain and nervous system respond to pain.

label: Clindamycin
description: A prescription antibiotic medication used to treat bacterial infections by inhibiting the growth of bacteria and reducing their ability to spread and cause infection.

label: Humira
description: A prescription medication used to treat various autoimmune diseases, including rheumatoid arthritis, Crohn''s disease, and psoriasis, by suppressing the immune system''s inflammatory response.

label: Enbrel
description: A prescription medication used to treat autoimmune diseases like rheumatoid arthritis and psoriasis by inhibiting a specific protein in the body that contributes to inflammation.

label: Clozapine
description: A prescription antipsychotic medication used to treat schizophrenia and reduce the risk of suicidal behavior in certain individuals with schizophrenia or schizoaffective disorder by affecting neurotransmitters in the brain.

label: Keppra
description: A prescription medication used to treat epilepsy by stabilizing electrical activity in the brain and reducing the frequency and severity of seizures.

label: Plavix
description: A prescription antiplatelet medication used to reduce the risk of blood clots and stroke in individuals with cardiovascular conditions by inhibiting the aggregation of platelets in the blood.

label: Tamiflu
description: A prescription antiviral medication used to treat influenza (the flu) by inhibiting the growth and spread of the influenza virus in the body, reducing the severity and duration of flu symptoms when taken early in the illness.

label: Nitrofurantoin
description: A prescription antibiotic medication primarily used to treat urinary tract infections (UTIs) by inhibiting the growth of bacteria in the urinary system.

label: Phentermine
description: A prescription medication used as an appetite suppressant to assist with weight loss in combination with diet and exercise by affecting the central nervous system to reduce hunger and increase feelings of fullness.
